"title": "2520: Jesus Christ, childhood of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2520",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>As an infant Jesus Christ was consecrated in the temple, accompanied by prophetic utterances regarding his future ministry. His childhood was characterised by a growth in wisdom and grace and, in particular, a strong desire to learn of God his Father and to understand the Scriptures.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ was consecrated as an infant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:22\">LUK 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:23-Luke2:24\">LUK 2:23–2:24</a></p>\n<h2>Indications of Jesus Christ's future ministry were revealed</h2>\n<h3>Through the words of Simeon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:30-Luke2:32\">LUK 2:30–2:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:25-Luke2:29\">LUK 2:25–2:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:34-Luke2:35\">LUK 2:34–2:35</a></p>\n<h3>Through the words of Anna</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:38\">LUK 2:38</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The visit of the Magi</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:1-Matt2:12\">MAT 2:1–2:12</a></p>\n<h2>The escape to Egypt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:13-Matt2:15\">MAT 2:13–2:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The return from Egypt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:19-Matt2:20\">MAT 2:19–2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:15\">MAT 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1\">HOS 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:21\">MAT 2:21</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ lives in Nazareth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:22-Matt2:23\">MAT 2:22–2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:39\">LUK 2:39</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ grows up</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:40\">LUK 2:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:52\">LUK 2:52</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ visited the temple</h2>\n<h3>He celebrates the Passover there</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:41-Luke2:42\">LUK 2:41–2:42</a></p>\n<h3>He stays behind in the temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:43-Luke2:45\">LUK 2:43–2:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:48-Luke2:50\">LUK 2:48–2:50</a></p>\n<h3>He displays his understanding of the Scriptures there</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:46-Luke2:47\">LUK 2:46–2:47</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The obedience of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:51\">LUK 2:51</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Mary and Joseph remember the sayings and events of Jesus Christ's childhood</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:19\">LUK 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:33\">LUK 2:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:51\">LUK 2:51</a></p>",
